  "body": "\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: autoscrolling to latest sent message stops working after you sent big message when you are somewhere in the middle of the chat, and then sent a small message at the end of history.\r\nOnly relogin helps to make autoscrolling works as before\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nautoscrolling works as before\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1) when you send message in current chat, app scrolls to the previous message\r\n2) when you switch to other chats, autoscrolling doesn't redirect to the latest message, or message content is partially overlapped.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Log in\r\n- Join any chat with history > 30 messages\r\n- Scroll to the middle of the history\r\n- Send a big message (for me it was 2282 chars)\r\n- Scroll fast to the end of history\r\n- Send any message \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: status desktop 09/10/2018\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSx\r\n* Video: http://take.ms/wCvve\r\n\r\n#### Logs : [StatusIm.txt](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2459867/StatusIm.txt)\r\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://api.monosnap.com/rpc/file/download?id=MbM2uQHMXqJoAFaOhX0ao1Ei2s8kbh&type=preview\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Monosnap screenshot tool</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://monosnap.com/file/MbM2uQHMXqJoAFaOhX0ao1Ei2s8kbh\">File \"screencast 2018-10-09 12-54-16.mp4\"</a></strong></div><div>Monosnap â€” the best tool to take & share your screenshots.</div></blockquote>",
